## Project Description
- Interactive book about AI Agents
- Main goal: teaching developers how to create and use AI Agents from scratch
- Target audience: developers, AI researchers, students

## Technology Stack
- Docusaurus 3.x for documentation and educational portal
- React for interactive components
- TypeScript for type safety
- Markdown/MDX for content
- i18n for localization (primary language: English)

## Project Structure:
cognitive-book/
├── docs/ - main content, markdown/mdx files
├── src/ - React components and theme settings
├── i18n/ - localization
├── docusaurus.config.ts - main configuration file
├── package.json - dependencies and scripts
├── sidebars.ts - sidebar navigation configuration
└── i18n/ru/ - Russian localization

## Content Formatting Rules
- Write in Russian in /i18n/ru/
- Write in English in /docs/
- Use Markdown for basic formatting
- Use MDX for complex components
- Store images in `/static/img/`
- Format code in ```` blocks

Working notes:
- In PowerShell on Windows, you cannot use the && operator. Let's execute commands separately.
- To start the server, use the command `npx docusaurus start --locale ru`
- Use English everywhere except /i18n/ru/. Use English in all React components.

